---
layout: content
title: AI Agent Skills
seoTitle: ESL AI Agent Skills — Copy & Download
description: Ready-to-use skill files for AI coding agents. Copy or download to give your AI assistant accurate ESL context.
name: AI Agent Skills
order: 6
tags: [nav, draft]
icon: sidebar/ai.svg
---

<p>
  The published <code>@exadel/esl</code> package now bundles one canonical AI skill with its reference docs.
</p>

<div class="skills-list">
  {% for skill in skills %}
  <article class="skill-card">
    <div class="skill-card-header">
      <h2 class="skill-card-title">{{ skill.name }}</h2>
      <p class="skill-card-desc">{{ skill.description | safe }}</p>
      <p class="skill-card-when"><b>Use when:</b> {{ skill.when | safe }}</p>
    </div>
    <div class="skill-card-actions btn-group hide">
      <a class="btn btn-sm" href="/downloads/{{ skill.archive }}" download="{{ skill.archive }}">
        Download bundle archive
      </a>
    </div>

    <div class="skill-install-grid">
      <section>
        <h3>Install with skills CLI</h3>
        <pre><code>npx skills add {{ skill.package }}</code></pre>
        <p>
          Recommended flow when your AI tooling can install skills directly from a published npm package.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="hide">
        <h3>Install from npm</h3>
        <pre><code>npm i -D {{ skill.package }}</code></pre>
        <p>
          Then copy <code>node_modules/{{ skill.package }}/skills/esl/</code> into your tool-specific skills directory.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="hide">
        <h3>Manual bundle files</h3>
        <p>
          Download the archive to get <code>SKILL.md</code> and the bundled <code>references/</code> folder together.
          If you only need one file, use the per-file actions below.
        </p>
        <a class="btn btn-sm" href="/downloads/{{ skill.archive }}" download="{{ skill.archive }}">
          Download {{ skill.archive }}
        </a>
      </section>
    </div>

    <div class="skill-files-list">
      {% for file in skill.files %}
      <section class="skill-file-card">
        <div class="skill-file-card-header">
          <p class="skill-file-card-label">{{ file.label }}</p>
          <h3 class="skill-file-card-title">{{ file.name }}</h3>
          <p class="skill-file-card-desc">{{ file.description }}</p>
        </div>
        <div class="skill-file-card-actions btn-group">
          <button class="btn btn-sm" esl-d-skill-copy="/ai-skills/{{ file.file }}">
            Copy file
          </button>
          <a class="btn btn-sm" href="/ai-skills/{{ file.file }}" download="{{ file.name | replace('/', '-') }}">
            Download file
          </a>
        </div>
        <details class="skill-preview">
          <summary>Preview {{ file.name }}</summary>
          <div class="skill-preview-content">
            {% mdRender file.source %}
          </div>
        </details>
      </section>
      {% endfor %}
    </div>
  </article>
  {% endfor %}
</div>
